<node ID="A0F11C89-B20A-436E-97C7-3D2BBFF9DE2F" TEXT="Concepts" COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="6" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="037191E0-B8AE-4EA7-AFDD-0FD6D74FE2C2" TEXT="I. Pattern" COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="5" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="A66EF946-8DC2-42E4-89A1-C6AF64EBD41C" TEXT="You use building blocks and design patterns to solve your problems." COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="A8B75939-EE83-4BF6-9890-71DFBB578963" TEXT="Corollary: you have to know what problems you have to be solved." COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="3" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
</node>
<node ID="AC890DB8-2050-4417-96EF-65BA20F7DD53" TEXT="Design is about understanding the options you have (patterns) and how to merge them." COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="3E89BCBC-8BF1-4ABD-B6B4-6C12D7DE9706" TEXT="With practice, you will be able to pull patterns out of your pocket without needing to think about it." COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="3" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
