<node ID="7C954ED3-65D7-4D29-B84C-143E902F7DD0" TEXT="If users can assign a single verb, or a single task to a block of your content, then that&#8217;s a successful design." COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
</node>
<node ID="7AC21DE8-690E-4F1E-91F7-292DB125A278" TEXT="IV. Scaling up &#38; down" COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="5" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="8B42F370-6AEB-43B4-98B5-56B94EE5170C" TEXT="You will have to iterate, the right level and composition of simplicity may not be immediately apparent." COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
<node ID="34D124A7-9774-4B67-B989-39E1BB8AA670" TEXT="How do you counter the danger of the &#8220;idea branching&#8221; process?" COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="7CE044C1-11D2-49FD-8E0C-582918759EBC" TEXT="as you think through the user process, new features will suggest themselves" COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="3" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
<node ID="556CB2AA-1D2B-4A6E-839E-58F2ECADB86F" TEXT="idea branching and converging may happen at the same time" COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="3" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="DF2DB85E-64D6-4CA4-8597-FFE902F43838" TEXT="as options continue to grow, may also be trimming / winnowing" COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="2" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
</node>
</node>
<node ID="BDD3C951-AFCA-4393-9390-C72B2C60DBD7" TEXT="Once you have the full task list, revisit the one-pager." COLOR="#36342E" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><arrowlink ID="Arrow_ID_BDD3C951-AFCA-4393-9390-C72B2C60DBD7_AADAB53E-6B23-4DAD-9372-417C75CDBC91" DESTINATION="AADAB53E-6B23-4DAD-9372-417C75CDBC91" STARTARROW="None" COLOR="#9B9EEA" ENDARROW="Default" /></node>
</node>
</node>
<node ID="63604E31-3DBB-4120-AC21-7B2D59647CE2" TEXT="Q &#38; A" COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="6" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="59381A74-80D0-4714-9D0F-E2432E0D67FF" TEXT="How do you know what the scanlines are? Are they based on research, or intuition?" COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="5" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="8882C623-4891-4005-A9DC-FEEFA9D753E0" TEXT="Used to be working at a company with eye-tracking." COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
<node ID="609561DF-2E4E-421F-BB60-51B40DBE33E3" TEXT="If eye-tracking is not available, may use a qualitative approach instead." COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="E725FA47-5350-4A2E-ADFF-52CD2243B004" TEXT="e.g., users begin with Task A vs. Task B &#8212; so they probably see Task A first" COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="3" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
<node ID="22FC16DE-486E-4F92-A5EE-E38CED9CAF6D" TEXT="designers may have an intuitive (but subjective) idea of it" COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="3" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
</node>
</node>
<node ID="421059B2-EF0D-4F4F-9507-95BD757749F0" TEXT="Do you use personas / are they useful for the approach you described here?" COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="5" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="51468B8E-931F-4C7E-A8A3-271BB0D388E9" TEXT="Yes, personas are useful." COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
<node ID="C5F51416-706E-4219-A0BD-CC20D3CB318A" TEXT="However, depending on the business culture, it can be hard to get agreement on whether the personas you come up with are truly representative / the &#8220;right&#8221; personas." COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="right" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#159588" WIDTH="4" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
</node>
</node>
<node ID="AAF71252-8F7B-41E0-B1C7-813008829223" TEXT="Follow-up session with more technical details" COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="left" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="6" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /><node ID="56A7E8E4-B651-46B8-8230-9AFA1E244F72" TEXT="Wed 10:45 AM - Mobile Interaction Design" COLOR="#36342D" POSITION="left" STYLE="fork"><edge COLOR="#238B21" WIDTH="5" /><font NAME="HelveticaNeue" SIZE="21" /></node>
</node>
</node>
</map>
